Devastating conflicts, violence and persecution in places like Syria and South Sudan left a record 65.6 million people uprooted from their homes by the end of 2016, the UN said Monday.&#8220;At the end of 2016, there were 65.6 million people forcibly displaced worldwide,&#8221; the UN refugee agency said in a statement, stressing that this was a &#8220;new unprecedented high.&#8221;-AFP